Trying to remember what it was like capturing the castle for @magnolia @joannagaines and it’s all a bit of a blur! Everywhere I looked there was another opportunity for an amazing image. So many beautiful details, the colors, the ceilings, the windows….For an interior photographer it was a dream. It took several long days and a great team making everything perfect and we captured a lot of beautiful design. 
I highly recommend watching Fixer Upper: The Castle if you haven’t already. And then check out all the before and afters and design resources on the Magnolia blog! 

These images are from the Drawing room located at the front on the castle with it’s gorgeous fireplace and windows! Also LOVE the paint color!

A year ago I was on a shoot for @woodardfurniture in the Hamptons. The creative director @cadamhallmark and I got to stay with @jeanliudesign at her beautiful East Hampton home. After our last day of shooting we came back here and of course being so inspired by her lovely home and the gorgeous natural light, I unpacked my camera and the three of us did an impromptu shoot together. Just a camera and tripod, and Jean’s elegant everyday styling. Thank you Jean for being a wonderful host and for letting me grab photos around your home!

New work for Hearth & Hand with @magnolia for @target. Beautiful home decor products that launched for @joannagaines autumn collection. 

Always love being apart of these shoots with our amazing team! Had a lot of fun creating such cozy scenes for the season!

Lisa Petrole is a Canadian/American freelance photographer specializing in interior design, architectural, and lifestyle photography.
Lisa's admiration of innovative design is what inspires her photography; and she loves working with designers and art directors that are pushing the boundaries of their field. Her goal is to capture visuals that match the level of creativity and craftsmanship of the work she photographs, bringing it to the world through editorials and advertising. Lisa is based in Dallas and regularly travels for shoots across North America.
